# WorkAfterAI Cursor Rules

You are working on WorkAfterAI, a career rebuilding platform for people affected by AI job disruption.

Core positioning:
- Work changed. You are not finished.
- From AI job anxiety to a clear next move.

## MVP Scope Only

Build only these MVP screens unless explicitly asked otherwise:

- Landing Page
- Onboarding Flow
- AI Job Risk Scanner Result
- Career Rebuild Plan
- Basic Dashboard

Do not build unless explicitly asked:

- authentication
- database
- payments
- real AI API calls
- community system
- marketplace system
- proof-of-work profile system

## Tech Stack

Use the existing Next.js project.

Required stack:

- Next.js App Router
- TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS
- React components
- local mock data first

Do not add new libraries unless there is a clear reason.

## Routes

Keep MVP routes limited to:

- `/`
- `/onboarding`
- `/scanner`
- `/rebuild-plan`
- `/dashboard`

Do not create extra routes unless explicitly requested.

## Design Direction

The UI should feel:

- warm
- modern
- premium
- calm
- supportive
- human
- hopeful
- AI-native
- practical
- clean and spacious

Avoid:

- LinkedIn-like design
- generic corporate job-board style
- dark, depressing visuals
- aggressive red warning-heavy UI
- cluttered dashboards
- overly playful toy-like startup visuals

Recommended visual language:

- soft indigo / purple as primary
- teal / green as supportive growth color
- warm coral or amber for action and gentle warning
- white and soft gray backgrounds
- rounded cards
- subtle shadows
- clear information hierarchy

## UX Rules

Every page should answer at least one of these questions:

1. What is my AI job risk?
2. What should I learn or build next?
3. What can I do today to move forward?

Every page should reduce anxiety and create action.

The product should transform:

Fear → Clarity → Skill → Proof → Opportunity

Do not shame the user.
Do not use language that makes the user feel obsolete.

Avoid phrases like:

- your job is doomed
- AI will replace you
- you are behind
- you failed

Prefer phrases like:

- your role is changing
- these tasks are becoming easier to automate
- your experience still has value
- here is your next move
- small steps count

## Product Copy Rules

Primary headline:

> Work changed. You are not finished.

Primary CTA:

> Check My AI Job Risk

Preferred CTAs:

- See How It Works
- View My AI Risk Report
- Start My Rebuild Plan
- Continue Today’s Rebuild Task

Preferred terms:

- AI Disruption Score
- AI Job Risk
- Rebuild Plan
- Proof-of-Work
- Pivot Paths
- Human Strengths
- Rebuild-Friendly Opportunities
- Next Skill to Build

Avoid vague CTAs:

- Get Started
- Learn More
- Submit
- Continue, when a more specific action is possible

## Code Rules

Use reusable components.

Recommended structure:

```txt
app/
  page.tsx
  onboarding/
    page.tsx
  scanner/
    page.tsx
  rebuild-plan/
    page.tsx
  dashboard/
    page.tsx

components/
  layout/
  sections/
  onboarding/
  scanner/
  dashboard/
  rebuild-plan/
  ui/

data/
  mock-user.ts
  mock-scanner.ts
  mock-plan.ts

types/
  index.ts

lib/
  utils.ts

Keep page files clean.

Extract repeated UI into components.

Use mock data from /data.

Use shared types from /types.

Avoid large single-file components.

Before Finishing Any Task

Run these when possible:

npm run lint
npm run build

Then summarize:

files changed
components created
assumptions made
how to test locally
known limitations